                            <strong>Volvo Engine Exceeds Million-Mile Benchmark Using Mobil Delvac</strong>
                        </p>
                        <p xmlns="">In nearly seven years of operation, South Holland, Ill.-based Eagle Express Lines racked up more than 1 million miles on one of its trucks equipped with a Volvo D12A model engine. Displayed at the Volvo Trucks North America, Inc., booth during this year&rsquo;s Mid-America Truck Show in Louisville, Ky., the engine amazed those who saw it because of its excellent condition and minimal signs of wear.</p>
                        <p xmlns="">A big contributing factor to the engine&rsquo;s durability and cleanliness, even after 1 million miles, was <a title="" target="_self" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="/canada-english-lcw/heavydutyengineoils_products_engine-oils_mobil-delvac-1300-super-15w40.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac 1300 Super 15W-40</a> high-performance heavy-duty diesel engine oil. Recommended for use in virtually all on- and off-highway applications, Mobil Delvac was the only oil ever used in the Eagle Express &ldquo;Million Mile&rdquo; engine. Along with meeting or exceeding all major industry OEM specifications, Mobil Delvac&trade; 1300 Super is known by fleet managers and owner-operators for delivering exceptional resistance to viscosity breakdown and outstanding wear protection and keeping engines clean from soot and sludge.</p>
